Idiosomal dorsum ( fig. 5 ,
1
) similar with that of female, but setae relatively shorter and less variable in length and shape. Setae si , c 1 , c 2 , cp , d 1 , d 2 , e 1 and h 1 blunt-ended.

Idiosomal venter ( fig. 5 ,
2
). Coxal apodemes as in female. Aedeagus very short, supported by arch-like structure. Genital papillae as in female, but smaller; setae p 1 – p 3 needle-like, setae h 2 blunt-ended. Setae p 3 situated just anteriad to adanal suckers. An area around setae h 2 , h 3 , p 1 , p 2 with weak but distinct sclerotization. Adanal suckers situated near anterior end of anal opening.

Legs ( fig. 6 ). Similar with that of female, except solenidia ω 1 on tarsus I and ω on tarsus II distinctly longer, solenidion ω 3 distinctly longer than ω 2 and situated near anterior end of the tarsus I; tarsus IV with setae d and e sucker-like, d in basal part of tarsus, e in distal. The length of solenidia on legs I–IV: leg I ( fig. 6 ,
1
